Common edge distribution c(n,k)/n!:
  n       k=0       k=1       k=2       k=3       k=4       k=5       k=6         Σ
  3         0         2         1         ·         ·         ·         ·         3
  4         2         5         3         1         ·         ·         ·        11
  5        14        20        14         4         1         ·         ·        53
  6        90       115        72        26         5         1         ·       309
  7       646       790       467       168        41         6         1      2119

=== Column analysis ===
k = n-1: always 1 (only the identity pair)
k = n-2: [2, 3, 4, 5, 6] = n-1
  Why: one edge differs. Choose which of n-1 edges to drop (n-1 choices),
  and the replacement must be compatible. Exactly 1 valid replacement each time.
k = n-3: [5, 14, 26, 41]
  Differences: [9, 12, 15]
  Second differences: [3, 3]
  Fit: c(n, n-3)/n! = (3n² - 9n - 2)/2
    n=4: predicted=5, actual=5, match=✓
    n=5: predicted=14, actual=14, match=✓
    n=6: predicted=26, actual=26, match=✓
    n=7: predicted=41, actual=41, match=✓

k = n-4: [20, 72, 168]
  Differences: [52, 96]

k = 0 (no common edges): [0, 2, 14, 90, 646]
  c(5,0)/c(4,0) = 7.0000
  c(6,0)/c(5,0) = 6.4286
  c(7,0)/c(6,0) = 7.1778

